---
import Layout from "@/layouts/main.astro"
import { Navbar } from "@/components/Navbar"
import { Footer } from "@/components/Footer"
import { absoluteUrl, breadcrumbJsonLd, organizationJsonLd } from "@/lib/seo"
---

<Layout
  seo={{
    title: "Terms of Service - LobbyStack",
    description:
      "Terms of Service for LobbyStack, the business AI receptionist platform for calls, SMS, booking, routing, and follow-up workflows.",
    canonicalPath: "/terms/",
    noindex: true,
    jsonLd: [
      organizationJsonLd(),
      breadcrumbJsonLd([
        { name: "Home", path: "/" },
        { name: "Terms of Service", path: "/terms/" },
      ]),
      {
        "@context": "https://schema.org",
        "@type": "WebPage",
        "@id": absoluteUrl("/terms/#webpage"),
        name: "Terms of Service - LobbyStack",
        url: absoluteUrl("/terms/"),
        description:
          "Terms of Service for LobbyStack, the business AI receptionist platform for calls, SMS, booking, routing, and follow-up workflows.",
      },
    ],
  }}
>
  <Navbar />
  <main class="bg-background text-foreground">
    <section class="border-b border-border/60">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 py-16 md:py-20">
        <p class="text-sm font-medium text-muted-foreground">
          Last updated: May 11, 2026
        </p>
        <h1 class="mt-4 text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight md:text-5xl">
          Terms of Service
        </h1>
        <p
          class="mt-6 max-w-3xl text-base leading-7 text-muted-foreground md:text-lg"
        >
          These Terms of Service govern access to and use of LobbyStack's hosted
          services, websites, paid plans, support, managed infrastructure, and
          related business AI receptionist workflows. Please read them carefully
          before using LobbyStack.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4 max-w-3xl text-sm leading-6 text-muted-foreground">
          These Terms are written in plain English for operational clarity, but
          they are not a substitute for independent legal advice. If you are
          unsure about your legal obligations, including telecommunications,
          privacy, anti-spam, or professional obligations, you should speak with
          qualified counsel.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section
      class="mx-auto grid max-w-6xl gap-10 px-6 py-12 md:grid-cols-[220px_1fr] md:py-16"
    >
      <aside class="hidden md:block">
        <nav class="sticky top-8 space-y-2 text-sm text-muted-foreground">
          <a class="block hover:text-foreground" href="#agreement">Agreement</a>
          <a class="block hover:text-foreground" href="#service">Service</a>
          <a class="block hover:text-foreground" href="#accounts">Accounts</a>
          <a class="block hover:text-foreground" href="#communications"
            >SMS and calls</a
          >
          <a class="block hover:text-foreground" href="#ai">AI limitations</a>
          <a class="block hover:text-foreground" href="#billing">Billing</a>
          <a class="block hover:text-foreground" href="#affiliate-program"
            >Affiliate program</a
          >
          <a class="block hover:text-foreground" href="#data">Data and IP</a>
          <a class="block hover:text-foreground" href="#risk">Risk allocation</a
          >
          <a class="block hover:text-foreground" href="#law">Governing law</a>
          <a class="block hover:text-foreground" href="#contact">Contact</a>
        </nav>
      </aside>

      <article class="legal-copy max-w-none">
        <section id="agreement">
          <h2>1. Agreement to these Terms</h2>
          <p>
            These Terms are a legal agreement between you and Lobbystack Inc.
            ("Lobbystack," "LobbyStack," "we," "our," or "us"). By accessing our
            website, creating an account, using the hosted LobbyStack service,
            purchasing a plan, enabling an add-on, or otherwise using the
            service, you agree to these Terms.
          </p>
          <p>
            If you use LobbyStack on behalf of a company, organization, or other
            legal entity, you represent that you have authority to bind that
            entity. In that case, "you" and "Customer" refer to that entity and
            its authorized users.
          </p>
          <p>
            Hosted LobbyStack accounts are intended for business and commercial
            use. They are not intended for personal, household, or consumer use.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="service">
          <h2>2. The LobbyStack service</h2>
          <p>
            LobbyStack is a business AI receptionist platform for calls, SMS,
            appointment booking, routing, summaries, contact capture, knowledge
            base responses, follow-up workflows, and related communications. The
            service may include hosted software, dashboards, phone numbers,
            voice and messaging features, integrations, automation tools,
            analytics, documentation, support, and related services.
          </p>
          <p>
            We may improve, modify, suspend, or discontinue parts of the service
            from time to time. Some features may be in beta, subject to provider
            approvals, limited by usage caps, or unavailable in some regions.
            Telecommunications features, including voice, SMS, phone numbers,
            A2P/10DLC registration, caller ID, carrier routing, and message
            deliverability, depend on third-party networks and providers.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="open-source">
          <h2>3. Open-source and self-hosted use</h2>
          <p>
            LobbyStack includes open-source software. Use, copying,
            modification, distribution, and self-hosting of the source code are
            governed by the applicable repository license, currently
            AGPL-3.0-only, and not by these hosted-service Terms except where
            these Terms expressly say otherwise.
          </p>
          <p>
            These Terms do govern LobbyStack Cloud, managed infrastructure,
            hosted accounts, paid plans, billing, support, trademarks, hosted
            documentation, websites, and any services we provide to you outside
            the open-source license. The LobbyStack name, logos, branding, and
            goodwill are not licensed for unrestricted use by the open-source
            license.
          </p>
          <p>
            If you self-host LobbyStack, you are responsible for your own
            infrastructure, security, provider accounts, telecommunications
            registrations, compliance, backups, billing setup, and end-user
            notices.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="accounts">
          <h2>4. Accounts, users, and customer responsibilities</h2>
          <p>
            You are responsible for keeping account credentials secure, managing
            your authorized users, maintaining accurate account and billing
            information, and promptly notifying us of unauthorized access. You
            are responsible for all activity under your account.
          </p>
          <p>
            You are responsible for configuring LobbyStack for your business,
            including business facts, services, prices, hours, locations,
            scripts, escalation rules, calendar connections, knowledge base
            content, transfer numbers, messaging instructions, and any human
            fallback procedures.
          </p>
          <p>
            You must not use LobbyStack to mislead callers or message
            recipients, impersonate another person or business, submit false
            registration information, violate third-party rights, or process
            information that you are not legally permitted to process.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="acceptable-use">
          <h2>5. Acceptable use</h2>
          <p>You must not use LobbyStack to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              Send spam, phishing, fraudulent, deceptive, or unlawful messages.
            </li>
            <li>Send content involving illegal goods or services.</li>
            <li>Harass, threaten, abuse, or discriminate against anyone.</li>
            <li>Transmit malware or attempt to compromise the service.</li>
            <li>
              Bypass security, usage limits, billing, registration, or provider
              rules.
            </li>
            <li>
              Use the service for emergency dispatch or life-safety response.
            </li>
            <li>
              Make regulated professional decisions without qualified human
              review.
            </li>
            <li>
              Use the service in a way that could harm telecommunications
              networks, carriers, providers, LobbyStack, or other users.
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            We may suspend or limit the service if we believe your use violates
            these Terms, provider requirements, law, or creates risk for
            LobbyStack, providers, carriers, users, or third parties.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="communications">
          <h2>6. Voice, SMS, and telecommunications compliance</h2>
          <p>
            LobbyStack can support voice calls and SMS notifications. These
            features are subject to carrier rules,
            telecommunications laws, anti-spam laws, provider terms, campaign
            registration requirements, message filtering, number availability,
            and usage restrictions.
          </p>
          <h3>LobbyStack SMS program</h3>
          <p>
            Program name: LobbyStack. LobbyStack messages are non-marketing
            operational and conversational messages related to business
            communications, customer inquiries, appointments, missed-call
            follow-up, service updates, support requests, routing,
            confirmations, reminders, and related workflows. Message frequency
            varies based on your interactions with a business using LobbyStack.
            Message and data rates may apply. Messages may include links for
            booking, support, intake, business information, appointment
            management, or related service workflows.
          </p>
          <p>
            For help with LobbyStack SMS, reply <strong>HELP</strong> where supported
            or contact
            <a href="mailto:support@lobbystack.com">support@lobbystack.com</a>.
            To stop receiving SMS messages from a LobbyStack-powered sender,
            reply <strong>STOP</strong>. After you opt out, you may receive a
            confirmation message, and no further SMS messages will be sent
            unless you opt in again where permitted. Carriers are not liable for
            delayed or undelivered messages.
          </p>
          <h3>Your compliance responsibilities</h3>
          <p>
            You are responsible for obtaining and documenting all required
            consents before sending calls or messages through LobbyStack,
            including consents required by CASL, TCPA, CTIA guidelines,
            A2P/10DLC rules, carrier rules, anti-spam laws, privacy laws, and
            any laws that apply to your business, your location, or your
            recipients. You must honor opt-out requests, keep consent records,
            provide truthful business and campaign information, and avoid
            prohibited or restricted message content.
          </p>
          <p>
            You must not use LobbyStack to send marketing, promotional,
            political, lending, age-gated, regulated, or sensitive messages
            unless the feature is enabled for that use case, all provider
            approvals are complete, and you have all required consents and legal
            authority.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="ai">
          <h2>7. AI limitations and human review</h2>
          <p>
            LobbyStack uses artificial intelligence and automation. AI outputs
            may be incomplete, inaccurate, delayed, unsafe for a particular use,
            or inconsistent with your expectations. You are responsible for
            reviewing, testing, and configuring the service before using it in
            production and for monitoring conversations that matter to your
            business.
          </p>
          <p>
            LobbyStack is not a substitute for emergency services, professional
            medical, legal, financial, or safety advice, or human judgment in
            sensitive situations. You must configure appropriate escalation and
            human fallback rules for urgent, sensitive, regulated, high-value,
            or complex conversations.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="billing">
          <h2>8. Plans, billing, taxes, and refunds</h2>
          <p>
            Paid plans, add-ons, setup fees, usage fees, metered charges, and
            taxes are described at checkout, in the app, or in an applicable
            order. Subscription plans renew automatically unless cancelled.
            Usage may be billed based on voice minutes, outbound call attempts,
            SMS segments, storage, phone numbers, or other metered units.
          </p>
          <p>
            You authorize us and our payment processor, currently Polar, to
            charge your payment method for recurring fees, usage fees, add-ons,
            setup fees, taxes, and other amounts due. If payment fails, we may
            suspend, limit, or terminate access. Unless required by law or
            expressly stated in a written agreement, fees are non-refundable.
            Cancellations take effect at the end of the current billing period,
            and usage fees already incurred remain payable.
          </p>
          <p>
            Prices may change. We will provide notice where required by law or
            where the change materially affects an active paid plan.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="affiliate-program">
          <h2>9. Affiliate Program</h2>
          <p>
            LobbyStack may offer an affiliate program that lets eligible users
            earn commissions for referring new customers to LobbyStack. If you
            participate in the affiliate program, this section applies in
            addition to the rest of these Terms.
          </p>
          <p>
            Unless we state otherwise in the service, eligible affiliates earn a
            20% commission on qualifying payments made by a referred customer
            during the first 12 months after attribution. Commissions are
            tracked through referral links or codes provided by LobbyStack.
            Attribution, eligibility, and commission calculations are determined
            by our records.
          </p>
          <p>
            Commissions are subject to a 30-day holding period and become
            eligible for payout only after the referred customer's payment has
            cleared the holding period and has not been refunded, charged back,
            disputed, reversed, credited, cancelled, or otherwise invalidated.
            Unpaid commissions may be voided, reduced, withheld, or reversed if
            the underlying payment or referral is not eligible.
          </p>
          <p>
            Affiliate payouts are made through PayPal using the PayPal email
            saved in the affiliate dashboard. The minimum payout
            threshold is USD $100 in eligible unpaid commissions. Payout timing
            may vary based on review, fraud checks, payment processor
            availability, accurate payout details, and other operational
            requirements. Affiliates are responsible for any taxes, reporting,
            forms, fees, currency conversion, and payment account issues that
            apply to their commissions or payouts.
          </p>
          <p>
            You must not refer yourself, create fake accounts, use misleading
            claims, spam, impersonate LobbyStack, bid on LobbyStack trademarks
            or confusingly similar terms in paid search, publish fake reviews,
            abuse coupons or discounts, generate artificial traffic, or promote
            LobbyStack in a way that violates law, third-party terms, platform
            rules, or these Terms. We may reject, suspend, or terminate
            affiliate participation and withhold unpaid commissions for fraud,
            abuse, non-compliance, or risk.
          </p>
          <p>
            Affiliates must clearly and conspicuously disclose that they may
            receive compensation when recommending LobbyStack, and must comply
            with applicable advertising, endorsement, anti-spam, privacy, and
            consumer protection laws. We may change, pause, or end the
            affiliate program, commission rates, attribution rules, holding
            periods, payout thresholds, payout methods, or eligibility
            requirements at any time, subject to applicable law.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="data">
          <h2>10. Customer content, data, and privacy</h2>
          <p>
            You retain ownership of your business content, customer data,
            recordings, transcripts, messages, knowledge base materials,
            appointments, and other content you submit to the service ("Customer
            Content"). You grant LobbyStack the rights needed to host, process,
            transmit, display, analyze, secure, and use Customer Content to
            provide, maintain, protect, troubleshoot, and improve the service.
          </p>
          <p>
            Our handling of personal information is described in our
            <a href="/privacy/">Privacy Policy</a>. You are responsible for
            providing your own notices to your customers and end users where
            required and for ensuring that you have the rights and consents
            needed for LobbyStack to process Customer Content.
          </p>
          <p>
            We may use de-identified, aggregated, or statistical information to
            operate, improve, secure, and analyze the service, provided it does
            not identify you, your users, or your end customers.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="third-party">
          <h2>11. Third-party services and integrations</h2>
          <p>
            LobbyStack relies on third-party services, including telephony and
            SMS providers, AI model providers, hosting and database providers,
            Polar or other payment processors, email and support tools,
            analytics providers, calendar providers, and other integrations.
            Your use of those features may be subject to third-party terms,
            limits, outages, filtering, approvals, and fees.
          </p>
          <p>
            We are not responsible for third-party services we do not control.
            We may change providers or integrations as needed to operate and
            improve LobbyStack.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="ip">
          <h2>12. Intellectual property</h2>
          <p>
            Except for Customer Content and open-source code governed by its
            applicable license, LobbyStack and its licensors own all rights,
            title, and interest in the hosted service, websites, designs,
            documentation, trademarks, logos, software, workflows, templates,
            and related materials. These Terms do not grant you ownership of
            LobbyStack or its branding.
          </p>
          <p>
            Feedback you provide may be used without restriction or compensation
            to you, but we will not identify you publicly as the source of
            feedback without your permission.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="termination">
          <h2>13. Suspension and termination</h2>
          <p>
            You may stop using LobbyStack at any time and may cancel paid plans
            through the app or by contacting support. We may suspend or
            terminate access if you violate these Terms, fail to pay, create
            legal or security risk, misuse telecommunications features, or if a
            provider or carrier requires us to do so.
          </p>
          <p>
            After termination, your right to use the hosted service ends. We may
            retain or delete data according to our Privacy Policy, backup
            practices, legal obligations, and any applicable written agreement.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="risk">
          <h2>14. Disclaimers, liability limits, and indemnity</h2>
          <p>
            To the maximum extent permitted by law, LobbyStack is provided "as
            is" and "as available." We do not guarantee uninterrupted service,
            error-free AI outputs, message delivery, call quality, carrier
            approval, number availability, business results, revenue, or that
            every caller or message recipient will be handled correctly.
          </p>
          <p>
            To the maximum extent permitted by law, Lobbystack Inc. and its
            affiliates, officers, directors, employees, contractors, and
            suppliers will not be liable for indirect, incidental, special,
            consequential, exemplary, or punitive damages, or for lost profits,
            lost revenue, lost data, loss of goodwill, business interruption, or
            replacement services.
          </p>
          <p>
            To the maximum extent permitted by law, our aggregate liability for
            all claims relating to the service is limited to the greater of CAD
            $100 or the amounts you paid to LobbyStack for the service in the
            three months before the event giving rise to the claim.
          </p>
          <p>
            You will defend, indemnify, and hold harmless Lobbystack Inc. from
            claims, damages, fines, costs, and expenses arising from your
            Customer Content, your use of the service, your end-user
            communications, your violation of law or provider requirements, your
            failure to obtain consent, or your breach of these Terms.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="law">
          <h2>15. Governing law and disputes</h2>
          <p>
            These Terms are governed by the laws of Quebec and the applicable
            federal laws of Canada, without regard to conflict of law rules.
            Subject to any rights that cannot be waived, the courts located in
            Quebec, Canada will have exclusive jurisdiction over disputes
            relating to these Terms or the service.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="changes">
          <h2>16. Changes to these Terms</h2>
          <p>
            We may update these Terms from time to time. If changes are
            material, we will provide reasonable notice, such as by posting a
            notice, updating the date above, emailing account contacts, or
            notifying users in the service. Continued use after changes become
            effective means you accept the updated Terms.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="contact">
          <h2>17. Contact</h2>
          <p>
            Questions about these Terms can be sent to Lobbystack Inc. at
            <a href="mailto:support@lobbystack.com">support@lobbystack.com</a>.
          </p>
        </section>
      </article>
    </section>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
